<AlteryxDocument yxmdVer="2025.2" RunE2="T">
  <Nodes>
    <Node ToolID="18">
      <GuiSettings Plugin="AlteryxGuiToolkit.TextBox.TextBox">
        <Position x="1043" y="80" width="360" height="324" />
      </GuiSettings>
      <Properties>
        <Configuration>
          <Text><![CDATA[Data Input & Cleaning: Imported orders.csv, products.csv, order_items.csv, and Customer.csv. Formatted transactional financial fields to numeric Double types and parsed the raw string order_purchase_timestamp into a standardized DateTime object. Cleaned string fields using the Data Cleansing tool to prevent whitespace mismatches.

Data Integration: Utilized a chain of Inner Join tools to seamlessly combine the datasets via shared relational keys (customer_id, order_id, and product_id) into a unified processing stream. Removed duplicate join columns to optimize performance.  

Calculated Fields: Applied a Formula tool to create three critical analytical variables:
 * Profit Margin (%) calculated using the business logic formula.
 * Discount Rate (%) derived to contrast catalog prices against finalized transaction amounts.
 * Order Year extracted from the parsed datetime tracking field.
 * Aggregation: Applied a Summarize tool to group data by category, year, and state, summing the transactional prices to output a structured total revenue matrix ready for Tableau ingestion.  ]]></Text>
          <Font name="Arial" size="8.25" style="0" />
          <TextColor name="Black" />
          <FillColor name="White" />
          <Shape shape="0" />
          <Justification Justification="3" />
        </Configuration>
        <Annotation DisplayMode="0">
          <Name />
          <DefaultAnnotationText />
          <Left value="False" />
        </Annotation>
      </Properties>
    </Node>
    <Node ToolID="45">
      <GuiSettings Plugin="AlteryxGuiToolkit.TextBox.TextBox">
        <Position x="1125" y="618" width="360" height="324" />
      </GuiSettings>
      <Properties>
        <Configuration>
          <Text>Data Input &amp; Cleaning: Imported customers.csv, order_payments.csv, order_reviews.csv, and orders.csv (which was used as a bridge table). Formatted financial fields (payment_value) to numeric Double types and review_score to Integers so calculations could be performed. Applied the Data Cleansing tool to remove null records, eliminate duplicates, and clean up extra spaces in the text fields.



Pre-Join Aggregation (Preventing Duplicates): Because a single order can have split payments or multiple reviews, joining the raw tables directly would have duplicated the data. Applied a Summarize tool before joining to group the data by order_id, summing the total payment values and averaging the review scores to ensure data accuracy.



Data Integration: Utilized a chain of Inner Join tools to successfully connect all four datasets. Linked customer demographics to the orders using customer_id, and then merged the aggregated payments and reviews using order_id. Unnecessary and duplicate columns (like Right_order_id) were deselected to keep the final dataset clean and optimized.



Final Aggregation: Applied a final Summarize tool to group the unified dataset by payment_type. Calculated three specific metrics ready for Tableau ingestion:



The exact number of unique orders per payment method (CountDistinct).

The average customer satisfaction score per payment method (Avg).


The total revenue generated by each payment method (Sum).</Text>
          <Font name="Arial" size="8.25" style="0" />
          <TextColor name="Black" />
          <FillColor name="White" />
          <Shape shape="0" />
          <Justification Justification="3" />
        </Configuration>
        <Annotation DisplayMode="0">
          <Name />
          <DefaultAnnotationText />
          <Left value="False" />
        </Annotation>
      </Properties>
    </Node>
    <Node ToolID="69">
      <GuiSettings Plugin="AlteryxGuiToolkit.TextBox.TextBox">
        <Position x="1171" y="1194" width="408" height="264" />
      </GuiSettings>
      <Properties>
        <Configuration>
          <Text>Relational Data Mapping: The primary orders dataset lacked direct vendor identifiers (seller_id). To resolve this, an intermediary order items table was integrated as a relational bridge, successfully mapping each specific customer transaction to its respective seller profile.

Boolean Aggregation Logic: Initial summarization logic inaccurately counted the total volume of orders rather than isolating the delayed ones. This was corrected by engineering a numeric binary flag (assigning 1 for delayed and 0 for on-time), allowing the system to accurately sum the true volume of late deliveries.

Interpreting Delivery Variance: The calculated average delivery delay consistently yielded negative values, which initially appeared to be a calculation error. Upon further data validation, it was established that a negative variance accurately represents early deliveries, indicating that the vast majority of packages are arriving ahead of their estimated schedule.</Text>
          <Font name="Arial" size="8.25" style="0" />
          <TextColor name="Black" />
          <FillColor name="White" />
          <Shape shape="0" />
          <Justification Justification="4" />
        </Configuration>
        <Annotation DisplayMode="0">
          <Name />
          <DefaultAnnotationText />
          <Left value="False" />
        </Annotation>
      </Properties>
    </Node>
